text: She was the only member of her family to surviv the Purge and 15 years later, she became Senator and wants the Purge gone when she becomes President. Her (I'm assuming) bodyguard, also, wants the Purge gone. She's in deep trouble when this year's Purge is on it's way because most of the population wants her gone. Her bodyguard hires a shit tone of protection... BUT OH WAIT! TRAITOR! Our two protagonists are now chased by a paid mercenary working for the government in place at the moment. A lot of unnecessary killings and jump scares happen until a group of good samaritans, who are poor people that work at some sort of gas station or convenience store, decide to help them. We have hope! She's going to be okay! NOPE. Car accident! She gets kidnapped by the government and she's brought to this shady cult-like church where they're going to torture her. She's going to die for sure, we saw her bodyguard and the godd samaritans hurt and probably some of 'em killed to spice the story. It's literally impossible that they come help h-.. Oh. They're here. A massive war starts in the church between the ,maybe, 5 people trying to help her and a hundred old people that are going to have guns hidden under their seats. Somehow the good guys win, until, the big boss(president) is not really dead and pulls her from the group with a knife on her throat. Unneccessary dialogue between the bodyguard and the president until, someone (a likeable supporting character) we thought was dead is not really dead and somehow found his way to this shady church kills the president from behind.  She went on to become president of the United States of 'Murica and she puts an end to the Purge and a trilogy of movies.  We will still find a way to make other Purge movies because we need the money.

text: The Purge is a satire (something nobody seems to have heard of). Of course it would never happen in real life. The movies are a critique on how the wealthy class abuses their power, specifically targeting the poor so that the upper class can flourish even more so. And the WHOLE POINT of the Purge is murder. Yes, other crimes are legal, but the act of killing is pivotal because it is a way of cleansing the the nation of poverty. The word Purge itself has a duel meaning: 1) to absolve personal pent up rage and 2) to remove a group of people from the country, those people being the lowest class.

text: Still trying to piece together how this trailer reveals the entire plot of the film. It's easy for us to figure out how, say, B v S might play out considering they're using characters based on pre existing properties, as well as planned films already announced. The Purge 3 hasn't really shown us anything significant that would spoil the film. I mean, I know what the movie is about now just not what's going to happen to all the protagonists. The same thing was done in The Purge 1 and 2's trailers: Shows the main protagonist in peril but some of them make it out okay. Just be patient and stop trying to figure out the movie like you're Sherlock Holmes on a goddamn crime scene.

text: I could make this movie much better.  There would be safe camps with an anti-purge communities and thousands of people sign up to it. All of the safe camps have there own 'special rules' to predict survivability. This one particular camp gives everyone a random number and a computer randomly selects two numbers that 'bond' during the purge. Whoever you are bonded to you must be handcuffed to them and survive together in the camp throughout the purge.  The handcuffs have a decent length chain between two bodies to allow minimum freedom but enough privacy. There are no weapons in the camps (except smuggled weapons) and at least 20% of the community are pro-purge. This would give the purgers the struggle of killing, knowing they would have to drag a body around and be instantly accused or in the other hand could be used by the purgers to play mind games with the community.   I could imagine this being pretty interesting, having at least one duo pro-purge and watching civilians having to drag bodies around or attempting to discard of them as they try escape the purge. The movie could easily have the scale tipped by adding the element of surprise from the pro-purgers pre setting weapons in the camp for themselves before hand or the camp gets under attack by other purgers who aren't handcuffed to make it more extreme.

text: Hello guys...  My name is Omar Khaled I'm from Egypt and I'm 15 years old.  for the last 8 - 9 years I've been teaching my self English and how to  communicate with other people and how to write and edit stories in  English and how to write quotes.  When I first saw Elizabeth I fell in love with her, not as a fan but I  felt something weird when I saw her and I read about her personality I  watched her works and I've seen her kindness filling my heart every time  I saw her. it has been my only dream to meet her and talk to her even  on the internet, because I wanna show her what I do, I wanna tell her my  words because that's what I'm good at. words.  I know you might find this funny, but I had a dream about Elizabeth and it was like this..  I was sitting on a table in a restaurant and suddenly I saw Elizabeth  and her son sitting on a table alone eating ice cream and laughing.. I  was shocked for seeing her, my dream, the woman I wanna make an  interview with sitting right there in front of me, then she looked at me  staring at her and I looked the other way because I was shy, then she  sent her son and he invited me to sit with them on their table.  he took my hand and we went to their table and then I met her... she was  like an angel looking at me.. then she noticed a pen in my hand and a  book and some papers.. she seemed interested in what I do, she asked me :  What are you writing? a book. I replied. she was surprised because you  don't see a 15 year old boy writing a book every day. she asked me: what  is your book talking about? I answered : my life.. she read some of it  and I saw her tears falling on her cheek and she said to me : that's  your life story? I said yes and that's my reality and I'm sorry for  making you cry... I had written that book with my tears and put all my  feelings in it.. after she finished reading a part of my book she hugged  me and told me : I'm sorry for what you've been through.. time passed  and we were talking non stop and having fun and I felt this dream like  it was real.. then she receieved a phone call and told me I'm sorry and I  wish I could spend more time with you... you're very talanted and kind  and the last thing she said when she was leaving was..Find me...I said  how? Then I woke up.... I really wish to meet her and talk to her in  real life and I need help doing that.... I really hope you can help me  and let her see this message... Thank you and god bless you all.
author: Omar Khaled

text: in this world full of war, destruction and tearing eyes here I stand looking to the sky trying to catch the wind with my eyes, wishing that one day my dream come true, trying to be the hero of my own story not the villain. My story isn't simple, it is a story full of adventure, sadness, fantasy, love and depression. My story is about the Egyptian reality and situations.. My story is told everyday. It's about my life and the normal people's life... what a cruel life! this life led us to the bottom, it made us monsters not humans, and when I realize that there's no way to make it right and there's no path to take but destruction, doom and war, when I think about the Egyptian streets I say to myself...: " What happened made us like this? what was the cause that made Egypt crumble and live in injustice and sickness? what happened to us made us kill each other for money and for stupid reasons? but still again questions without answers.. if there was a movie about our life it would win an Oscar in tragic moments category, because our reality is so painful and makes the heart cry out it's blood... There's nothing I can do to save my country but praying for god and hoping my life get better.. May God have mercy on Egypt
author: Omar Khaled
